Thank you for making these, LEGO! Just got my first two modular buildings as a gift from friends for my 30th birthday (Palace Cinema and Assembly Square) and I just spent month building it at nights and it was such an enjoyable experience. I have been fan of Lego since I was 3 when my dad got me wonderful 6354 Police Patrol set and I never stopped, but when I finally got to build these modular buildings I actually relieved my best childhood memories of building. To build real stuff at any point of the process (things like tables and stoves and oven and so on), that was just so wonderful and inspiring to make stuff of my own! Just wonderful! Please never stop releasing these modulars, especially as wonderful as this Diner!
Thank you for sharing you amazing experience with us! We feel so glad that you have been a LEGO fan since your are 3! :D
